FLOOR AMENDMENT
HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
State of Oklahoma
SPEAKER:
CHAIR:
I move to amend HB2588
Of the printed Bill
Page 2 Section 1 Lines 9
Of the Engrossed Bill
By inserting the following language after the period ".":
"For purposes of this act, a member of said owners association is deemed
to “physically reside” in the real estate development if the member
maintains an address for personal income tax purposes at a home or
dwelling within the owners association, and the member inhabits and
maintains the home or dwelling located at that address within the owners
association as the member’s fixed, permanent, and principal home for at
least ten (10) months, in the aggregate, during each calendar year in
which the member serves on the board. If at any time after the member is
elected to serve as a board member the member fails to meet or no longer
meets the requirements of physically residing in the real estate
development, that board member will be deemed to have automatically
resigned his or her position as a board member."
AMEND TITLE TO CONFORM TO AMENDMENTS
